{
  "video_id": "RKK7wGAYP6k",
  "title": "How language shapes the way we think | Lera Boroditsky",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12940.0,
      "end_time": 15515.0,
      "text": "So, I'll be speaking to you using language ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16900.0,
      "end_time": 17610.0,
      "text": "because I can."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17634.0,
      "end_time": 20787.0,
      "text": "This is one of these magical abilities that we humans have."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21114.0,
      "end_time": 25660.0,
      "text": "We can transmit really complicated thoughts to one another."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25479.0,
      "end_time": 29730.0,
      "text": "So what I'm doing right now is, I'm making sounds with my mouth"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29980.0,
      "end_time": 30313.0,
      "text": "as I'm exhaling."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30337.0,
      "end_time": 32685.0,
      "text": "I'm making tones and hisses and puffs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32709.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35719.0,
      "text": "and those are creating air vibrations in the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35743.0,
      "end_time": 38189.0,
      "text": "Those air vibrations are traveling to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 38213.0,
      "end_time": 39998.0,
      "text": "they're hitting your eardrums,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 40220.0,
      "end_time": 44602.0,
      "text": "and then your brain takes those vibrations from your eardrums"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44626.0,
      "end_time": 47379.0,
      "text": "and transforms them into thoughts."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48310.0,
      "end_time": 49182.0,
      "text": "I hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49206.0,
      "end_time": 50209.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50233.0,
      "end_time": 51390.0,
      "text": "I hope that's happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 51414.0,
      "end_time": 55990.0,
      "text": "So because of this ability, we humans are able to transmit our ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56140.0,
      "end_time": 58706.0,
      "text": "across vast reaches of space and time."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58730.0,
      "end_time": 63266.0,
      "text": "We're able to transmit knowledge across minds."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63290.0,
      "end_time": 66451.0,
      "text": "I can put a bizarre new idea in your mind right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 66475.0,
      "end_time": 67630.0,
      "text": "I could say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68367.0,
      "end_time": 71575.0,
      "text": "\"Imagine a jellyfish waltzing in a library"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 71599.0,
      "end_time": 73775.0,
      "text": "while thinking about quantum mechanics.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 73799.0,
      "end_time": 75197.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 75221.0,
      "end_time": 78249.0,
      "text": "Now, if everything has gone relatively well in your life so far,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 78273.0,
      "end_time": 80384.0,
      "text": "you probably haven't had that thought before."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80409.0,
      "end_time": 81411.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 81435.0,
      "end_time": 83167.0,
      "text": "But now I've just made you think it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 83191.0,
      "end_time": 84346.0,
      "text": "through language."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 84654.0,
      "end_time": 87378.0,
      "text": "Now of course, there isn't just one language in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 87402.0,
      "end_time": 90470.0,
      "text": "there are about 7,000 languages spoken around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90710.0,
      "end_time": 93231.0,
      "text": "And all the languages differ from one another in all kinds of ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93255.0,
      "end_time": 96345.0,
      "text": "Some languages have different sounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 96370.0,
      "end_time": 98890.0,
      "text": "they have different vocabularies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 98113.0,
      "end_time": 100152.0,
      "text": "and they also have different structures --"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 100176.0,
      "end_time": 102630.0,
      "text": "very importantly, different structures."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 102896.0,
      "end_time": 104880.0,
      "text": "That begs the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 104112.0,
      "end_time": 106723.0,
      "text": "Does the language we speak shape the way we think?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 106748.0,
      "end_time": 108320.0,
      "text": "Now, this is an ancient question."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 108344.0,
      "end_time": 111515.0,
      "text": "People have been speculating about this question forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 111539.0,
      "end_time": 113856.0,
      "text": "Charlemagne, Holy Roman emperor, said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 113880.0,
      "end_time": 116916.0,
      "text": "\"To have a second language is to have a second soul\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 116940.0,
      "end_time": 119443.0,
      "text": "strong statement that language crafts reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 119992.0,
      "end_time": 122982.0,
      "text": "But on the other hand, Shakespeare has Juliet say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 123600.0,
      "end_time": 124157.0,
      "text": "\"What's in a name?"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 124181.0,
      "end_time": 126515.0,
      "text": "A rose by any other name would smell as sweet.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127504.0,
      "end_time": 130557.0,
      "text": "Well, that suggests that maybe language doesn't craft reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 130925.00000000001,
      "end_time": 134932.0,
      "text": "These arguments have gone back and forth for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 135400.0,
      "end_time": 138131.0,
      "text": "But until recently, there hasn't been any data"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 138155.0,
      "end_time": 139711.0,
      "text": "to help us decide either way."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 140230.0,
      "end_time": 142682.0,
      "text": "Recently, in my lab and other labs around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 142706.0,
      "end_time": 144970.0,
      "text": "we've started doing research,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 144122.0,
      "end_time": 148559.0,
      "text": "and now we have actual scientific data to weigh in on this question."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 148918.0,
      "end_time": 151459.0,
      "text": "So let me tell you about some of my favorite examples."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 151846.0,
      "end_time": 155260.0,
      "text": "I'll start with an example from an Aboriginal community in Australia"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 155284.0,
      "end_time": 157120.0,
      "text": "that I had the chance to work with."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 157360.0,
      "end_time": 158779.0,
      "text": "These are the Kuuk Thaayorre people."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 158803.0,
      "end_time": 162597.0,
      "text": "They live in Pormpuraaw at the very west edge of Cape York."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 163351.0,
      "end_time": 165587.0,
      "text": "What's cool about Kuuk Thaayorre is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 165611.0,
      "end_time": 168668.0,
      "text": "in Kuuk Thaayorre, they don't use words like \"left\" and \"right,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 168693.0,
      "end_time": 171377.0,
      "text": "and instead, everything is in cardinal directions:"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 171401.0,
      "end_time": 172825.0,
      "text": "north, south, east and west."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 173425.0,
      "end_time": 175960.0,
      "text": "And when I say everything, I really mean everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 175984.0,
      "end_time": 177535.0,
      "text": "You would say something like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 177559.0,
      "end_time": 180710.0,
      "text": "\"Oh, there's an ant on your southwest leg.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 181178.0,
      "end_time": 183834.0,
      "text": "Or, \"Move your cup to the north-northeast a little bit.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 184404.0,
      "end_time": 187884.0,
      "text": "In fact, the way that you say \"hello\" in Kuuk Thaayorre is you say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 187908.0,
      "end_time": 189173.0,
      "text": "\"Which way are you going?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 189198.0,
      "end_time": 190530.0,
      "text": "And the answer should be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 191140.0,
      "end_time": 192786.0,
      "text": "\"North-northeast in the far distance."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 192810.0,
      "end_time": 194131.0,
      "text": "How about you?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 194155.0,
      "end_time": 197287.0,
      "text": "So imagine as you're walking around your day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 197311.0,
      "end_time": 198860.0,
      "text": "every person you greet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 198884.0,
      "end_time": 200954.0,
      "text": "you have to report your heading direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 200979.0,
      "end_time": 202158.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 202182.0,
      "end_time": 205512.0,
      "text": "But that would actually get you oriented pretty fast, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 205537.0,
      "end_time": 208497.0,
      "text": "Because you literally couldn't get past \"hello,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 208521.0,
      "end_time": 210595.0,
      "text": "if you didn't know which way you were going."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 211969.0,
      "end_time": 215460.0,
      "text": "In fact, people who speak languages like this stay oriented really well."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 215485.0,
      "end_time": 218410.0,
      "text": "They stay oriented better than we used to think humans could."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 218840.0,
      "end_time": 221692.0,
      "text": "We used to think that humans were worse than other creatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 221716.0,
      "end_time": 223432.0,
      "text": "because of some biological excuse:"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 223456.0,
      "end_time": 226780.0,
      "text": "\"Oh, we don't have magnets in our beaks or in our scales.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 226805.0,
      "end_time": 229747.0,
      "text": "No; if your language and your culture trains you to do it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 229771.0,
      "end_time": 231190.0,
      "text": "actually, you can do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 231440.0,
      "end_time": 234840.0,
      "text": "There are humans around the world who stay oriented really well."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 234108.0,
      "end_time": 236236.0,
      "text": "And just to get us in agreement"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 236260.0,
      "end_time": 238855.0,
      "text": "about how different this is from the way we do it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 238879.0,
      "end_time": 241643.0,
      "text": "I want you all to close your eyes for a second"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 242887.0,
      "end_time": 244240.0,
      "text": "and point southeast."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 244264.0,
      "end_time": 245974.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 245998.0,
      "end_time": 247576.0,
      "text": "Keep your eyes closed. Point."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 250950.0,
      "end_time": 252112.0,
      "text": "OK, so you can open your eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 252136.0,
      "end_time": 255915.0,
      "text": "I see you guys pointing there, there, there, there, there ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 256529.0,
      "end_time": 258406.0,
      "text": "I don't know which way it is myself --"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 258430.0,
      "end_time": 260940.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 260119.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261777.00000000003,
      "text": "You have not been a lot of help."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 261801.0,
      "end_time": 263118.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 263142.0,
      "end_time": 266620.0,
      "text": "So let's just say the accuracy in this room was not very high."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 266860.0,
      "end_time": 269446.0,
      "text": "This is a big difference in cognitive ability across languages, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 269470.0,
      "end_time": 272865.0,
      "text": "Where one group -- very distinguished group like you guys --"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 272889.0,
      "end_time": 274452.0,
      "text": "doesn't know which way is which,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 274476.0,
      "end_time": 275812.0,
      "text": "but in another group,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 275836.0,
      "end_time": 278126.0,
      "text": "I could ask a five-year-old and they would know."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 278150.0,
      "end_time": 279234.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 279258.0,
      "end_time": 282678.0,
      "text": "There are also really big differences in how people think about time."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 282702.0,
      "end_time": 286719.0,
      "text": "So here I have pictures of my grandfather at different ages."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 286743.0,
      "end_time": 289969.0,
      "text": "And if I ask an English speaker to organize time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 289994.0,
      "end_time": 291479.0,
      "text": "they might lay it out this way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 291503.0,
      "end_time": 292654.0,
      "text": "from left to right."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 292678.0,
      "end_time": 294509.0,
      "text": "This has to do with writing direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 294533.0,
      "end_time": 296559.0,
      "text": "If you were a speaker of Hebrew or Arabic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 296583.0,
      "end_time": 298873.0,
      "text": "you might do it going in the opposite direction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 298897.0,
      "end_time": 300460.0,
      "text": "from right to left."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 301578.0,
      "end_time": 303162.0,
      "text": "But how would the Kuuk Thaayorre,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 303187.0,
      "end_time": 305581.0,
      "text": "this Aboriginal group I just told you about, do it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 305605.0,
      "end_time": 307723.0,
      "text": "They don't use words like \"left\" and \"right.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 307747.0,
      "end_time": 309239.0,
      "text": "Let me give you hint."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 309263.0,
      "end_time": 311813.0,
      "text": "When we sat people facing south,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 311838.0,
      "end_time": 313696.0,
      "text": "they organized time from left to right."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 314391.0,
      "end_time": 316574.0,
      "text": "When we sat them facing north,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 316598.0,
      "end_time": 318573.0,
      "text": "they organized time from right to left."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 319260.0,
      "end_time": 321810.0,
      "text": "When we sat them facing east,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 321105.0,
      "end_time": 322845.0,
      "text": "time came towards the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 323608.0,
      "end_time": 324919.0,
      "text": "What's the pattern?"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 326560.0,
      "end_time": 327755.0,
      "text": "East to west, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 327779.0,
      "end_time": 331281.0,
      "text": "So for them, time doesn't actually get locked on the body at all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 331305.0,
      "end_time": 332845.0,
      "text": "it gets locked on the landscape."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 332869.0,
      "end_time": 334587.0,
      "text": "So for me, if I'm facing this way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 334611.0,
      "end_time": 335768.0,
      "text": "then time goes this way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 335792.0,
      "end_time": 338265.0,
      "text": "and if I'm facing this way, then time goes this way."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 338289.0,
      "end_time": 340289.0,
      "text": "I'm facing this way, time goes this way --"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 340313.0,
      "end_time": 344280.0,
      "text": "very egocentric of me to have the direction of time chase me around"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 344304.0,
      "end_time": 345943.0,
      "text": "every time I turn my body."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 346598.0,
      "end_time": 349245.0,
      "text": "For the Kuuk Thaayorre, time is locked on the landscape."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 349269.0,
      "end_time": 352880.0,
      "text": "It's a dramatically different way of thinking about time."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 352112.0,
      "end_time": 354230.0,
      "text": "Here's another really smart human trick."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 354470.0,
      "end_time": 356260.0,
      "text": "Suppose I ask you how many penguins are there."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 356958.0,
      "end_time": 360112.0,
      "text": "Well, I bet I know how you'd solve that problem if you solved it."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 360136.0,
      "end_time": 362963.0,
      "text": "You went, \"One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 362987.0,
      "end_time": 364151.0,
      "text": "You counted them."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 364175.0,
      "end_time": 365784.0,
      "text": "You named each one with a number,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 365808.0,
      "end_time": 368444.0,
      "text": "and the last number you said was the number of penguins."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 368468.0,
      "end_time": 371330.0,
      "text": "This is a little trick that you're taught to use as kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 371354.0,
      "end_time": 374405.0,
      "text": "You learn the number list and you learn how to apply it."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 374787.0,
      "end_time": 376233.0,
      "text": "A little linguistic trick."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 376804.0,
      "end_time": 378481.0,
      "text": "Well, some languages don't do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 378505.0,
      "end_time": 381654.0,
      "text": "because some languages don't have exact number words."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 382390.0,
      "end_time": 384936.0,
      "text": "They're languages that don't have a word like \"seven\""
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 384960.0,
      "end_time": 386361.0,
      "text": "or a word like \"eight.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 387330.0,
      "end_time": 389691.0,
      "text": "In fact, people who speak these languages don't count,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 389715.0,
      "end_time": 392712.0,
      "text": "and they have trouble keeping track of exact quantities."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 392736.0,
      "end_time": 396664.0,
      "text": "So, for example, if I ask you to match this number of penguins"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 396689.0,
      "end_time": 398953.0,
      "text": "to the same number of ducks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 398977.0,
      "end_time": 401121.0,
      "text": "you would be able to do that by counting."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 401145.0,
      "end_time": 405000.0,
      "text": "But folks who don't have that linguistic trick can't do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 407653.0,
      "end_time": 410807.0,
      "text": "Languages also differ in how they divide up the color spectrum --"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 410831.0,
      "end_time": 411981.0,
      "text": "the visual world."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 412348.0,
      "end_time": 414500.0,
      "text": "Some languages have lots of words for colors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 414524.0,
      "end_time": 416888.0,
      "text": "some have only a couple words, \"light\" and \"dark.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 416912.0,
      "end_time": 420534.0,
      "text": "And languages differ in where they put boundaries between colors."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 420559.0,
      "end_time": 423774.0,
      "text": "So, for example, in English, there's a word for blue"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 423798.0,
      "end_time": 426933.0,
      "text": "that covers all of the colors that you can see on the screen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 426957.0,
      "end_time": 428962.0,
      "text": "but in Russian, there isn't a single word."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 428987.0,
      "end_time": 431193.0,
      "text": "Instead, Russian speakers have to differentiate"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 431217.0,
      "end_time": 432688.0,
      "text": "between light blue, \"goluboy,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 432712.0,
      "end_time": 434288.0,
      "text": "and dark blue, \"siniy.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 435138.0,
      "end_time": 439121.0,
      "text": "So Russians have this lifetime of experience of, in language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 439145.0,
      "end_time": 441140.0,
      "text": "distinguishing these two colors."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 441380.0,
      "end_time": 445100.0,
      "text": "When we test people's ability to perceptually discriminate these colors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 445250.0,
      "end_time": 447546.0,
      "text": "what we find is that Russian speakers are faster"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 447570.0,
      "end_time": 449128.0,
      "text": "across this linguistic boundary."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 449152.0,
      "end_time": 451433.0,
      "text": "They're faster to be able to tell the difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 451458.0,
      "end_time": 452916.0,
      "text": "between a light and dark blue."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 453299.0,
      "end_time": 456563.0,
      "text": "And when you look at people's brains as they're looking at colors --"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 456587.0,
      "end_time": 459921.0,
      "text": "say you have colors shifting slowly from light to dark blue --"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 460798.0,
      "end_time": 465250.0,
      "text": "the brains of people who use different words for light and dark blue"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 465274.0,
      "end_time": 468784.0,
      "text": "will give a surprised reaction as the colors shift from light to dark,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 468808.0,
      "end_time": 471990.0,
      "text": "as if, \"Ooh, something has categorically changed,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 472140.0,
      "end_time": 474460.0,
      "text": "whereas the brains of English speakers, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 474484.0,
      "end_time": 476623.0,
      "text": "that don't make this categorical distinction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 476648.0,
      "end_time": 477844.0,
      "text": "don't give that surprise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 477868.0,
      "end_time": 479951.0,
      "text": "because nothing is categorically changing."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 482540.0,
      "end_time": 484558.0,
      "text": "Languages have all kinds of structural quirks."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 484582.0,
      "end_time": 485919.0,
      "text": "This is one of my favorites."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 485943.0,
      "end_time": 488375.0,
      "text": "Lots of languages have grammatical gender,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 488399.0,
      "end_time": 493290.0,
      "text": "so every noun gets assigned a gender, often masculine or feminine."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 493530.0,
      "end_time": 495110.0,
      "text": "And these genders differ across languages."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 495134.0,
      "end_time": 499675.0,
      "text": "So, for example, the sun is feminine in German but masculine in Spanish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 499699.0,
      "end_time": 501470.0,
      "text": "and the moon, the reverse."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 501634.0,
      "end_time": 505960.0,
      "text": "Could this actually have any consequence for how people think?"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 505120.0,
      "end_time": 509114.0,
      "text": "Do German speakers think of the sun as somehow more female-like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 509138.0,
      "end_time": 511440.0,
      "text": "and the moon somehow more male-like?"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 511767.0,
      "end_time": 513673.0,
      "text": "Actually, it turns out that's the case."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 513697.0,
      "end_time": 519120.0,
      "text": "So if you ask German and Spanish speakers to, say, describe a bridge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 519144.0,
      "end_time": 520580.0,
      "text": "like the one here --"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 520604.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523953.00000000006,
      "text": "\"bridge\" happens to be grammatically feminine in German,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 523977.0,
      "end_time": 526132.0,
      "text": "grammatically masculine in Spanish --"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 526157.0,
      "end_time": 530475.0,
      "text": "German speakers are more likely to say bridges are \"beautiful,\" \"elegant\""
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 530499.0,
      "end_time": 532626.0,
      "text": "and stereotypically feminine words."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 532650.0,
      "end_time": 535159.0,
      "text": "Whereas Spanish speakers will be more likely to say"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 535183.0,
      "end_time": 536729.0,
      "text": "they're \"strong\" or \"long,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 536753.0,
      "end_time": 538139.0,
      "text": "these masculine words."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 540849.0,
      "end_time": 542529.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 543396.0,
      "end_time": 547517.0,
      "text": "Languages also differ in how they describe events, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 548600.0,
      "end_time": 550406.0,
      "text": "You take an event like this, an accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 550430.0,
      "end_time": 553218.0,
      "text": "In English, it's fine to say, \"He broke the vase.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 553869.0,
      "end_time": 556413.0,
      "text": "In a language like Spanish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 556437.0,
      "end_time": 559284.0,
      "text": "you might be more likely to say, \"The vase broke,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 559308.0,
      "end_time": 560869.0,
      "text": "or, \"The vase broke itself.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 561332.0,
      "end_time": 564554.0,
      "text": "If it's an accident, you wouldn't say that someone did it."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 564578.0,
      "end_time": 567983.0,
      "text": "In English, quite weirdly, we can even say things like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 568800.0,
      "end_time": 569255.0,
      "text": "\"I broke my arm.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 569953.0,
      "end_time": 571786.0,
      "text": "Now, in lots of languages,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 571811.0,
      "end_time": 574982.0,
      "text": "you couldn't use that construction unless you are a lunatic"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 575600.0,
      "end_time": 577135.0,
      "text": "and you went out looking to break your arm --"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 577159.0,
      "end_time": 578161.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 578185.0,
      "end_time": 579335.0,
      "text": "and you succeeded."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 579360.0,
      "end_time": 582624.0,
      "text": "If it was an accident, you would use a different construction."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 582648.0,
      "end_time": 584453.0,
      "text": "Now, this has consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 584477.0,
      "end_time": 588665.0,
      "text": "So, people who speak different languages will pay attention to different things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 588689.0,
      "end_time": 592940.0,
      "text": "depending on what their language usually requires them to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 592119.0,
      "end_time": 596291.0,
      "text": "So we show the same accident to English speakers and Spanish speakers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 596315.0,
      "end_time": 599600.0,
      "text": "English speakers will remember who did it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 600525.0,
      "end_time": 603939.0,
      "text": "because English requires you to say, \"He did it; he broke the vase.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 603963.0,
      "end_time": 607165.0,
      "text": "Whereas Spanish speakers might be less likely to remember who did it"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 607190.0,
      "end_time": 608341.0,
      "text": "if it's an accident,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 608365.0,
      "end_time": 611194.0,
      "text": "but they're more likely to remember that it was an accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 611218.0,
      "end_time": 613654.0,
      "text": "They're more likely to remember the intention."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 613678.0,
      "end_time": 616761.0,
      "text": "So, two people watch the same event,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 616785.0,
      "end_time": 618866.0,
      "text": "witness the same crime,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 618890.0,
      "end_time": 621936.0,
      "text": "but end up remembering different things about that event."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 622564.0,
      "end_time": 625823.0,
      "text": "This has implications, of course, for eyewitness testimony."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 626590.0,
      "end_time": 628952.0,
      "text": "It also has implications for blame and punishment."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 628976.0,
      "end_time": 630783.0,
      "text": "So if you take English speakers"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 630807.0,
      "end_time": 632971.0,
      "text": "and I just show you someone breaking a vase,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 632995.0,
      "end_time": 636850.0,
      "text": "and I say, \"He broke the vase,\" as opposed to \"The vase broke,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 637504.0,
      "end_time": 639417.0,
      "text": "even though you can witness it yourself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 639441.0,
      "end_time": 640709.0,
      "text": "you can watch the video,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 640733.0,
      "end_time": 642895.0,
      "text": "you can watch the crime against the vase,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 644157.0,
      "end_time": 645924.0,
      "text": "you will punish someone more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 645948.0,
      "end_time": 648800.0,
      "text": "you will blame someone more if I just said, \"He broke it,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 648825.0,
      "end_time": 650318.0,
      "text": "as opposed to, \"It broke.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 650931.0,
      "end_time": 654254.0,
      "text": "The language guides our reasoning about events."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 655996.0,
      "end_time": 658882.0,
      "text": "Now, I've given you a few examples"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 658906.0,
      "end_time": 662632.0,
      "text": "of how language can profoundly shape the way we think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 662657.0,
      "end_time": 664832.0,
      "text": "and it does so in a variety of ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 664856.0,
      "end_time": 666787.0,
      "text": "So language can have big effects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 666811.0,
      "end_time": 668553.0,
      "text": "like we saw with space and time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 668577.0,
      "end_time": 670483.0,
      "text": "where people can lay out space and time"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 670507.0,
      "end_time": 673747.0,
      "text": "in completely different coordinate frames from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 674781.0,
      "end_time": 677150.0,
      "text": "Language can also have really deep effects --"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 677390.0,
      "end_time": 679223.0,
      "text": "that's what we saw with the case of number."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 679572.0,
      "end_time": 681615.0,
      "text": "Having count words in your language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 681639.0,
      "end_time": 682859.0,
      "text": "having number words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 682883.0,
      "end_time": 685444.0,
      "text": "opens up the whole world of mathematics."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 685468.0,
      "end_time": 687971.0,
      "text": "Of course, if you don't count, you can't do algebra,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 687995.0,
      "end_time": 689559.0,
      "text": "you can't do any of the things"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 689583.0,
      "end_time": 692326.0,
      "text": "that would be required to build a room like this"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 692350.0,
      "end_time": 694354.0,
      "text": "or make this broadcast, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 694836.0,
      "end_time": 697699.0,
      "text": "This little trick of number words gives you a stepping stone"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 697723.0,
      "end_time": 699204.0,
      "text": "into a whole cognitive realm."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 700420.0,
      "end_time": 702714.0,
      "text": "Language can also have really early effects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 702739.0,
      "end_time": 705609.0,
      "text": "what we saw in the case of color."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 706205.0,
      "end_time": 708699.0,
      "text": "These are really simple, basic, perceptual decisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 708723.0,
      "end_time": 711830.0,
      "text": "We make thousands of them all the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 711107.0,
      "end_time": 712924.0,
      "text": "and yet, language is getting in there"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 712948.0,
      "end_time": 717279.0,
      "text": "and fussing even with these tiny little perceptual decisions that we make."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 718787.0,
      "end_time": 720646.0,
      "text": "Language can have really broad effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 720670.0,
      "end_time": 723897.0,
      "text": "So the case of grammatical gender may be a little silly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 723922.0,
      "end_time": 727755.0,
      "text": "but at the same time, grammatical gender applies to all nouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 728610.0,
      "end_time": 730350.0,
      "text": "That means language can shape how you're thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 730374.0,
      "end_time": 733261.0,
      "text": "about anything that can be named by a noun."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 734185.0,
      "end_time": 735513.0,
      "text": "That's a lot of stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 736449.0,
      "end_time": 739705.0,
      "text": "And finally, I gave you an example of how language can shape things"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 739730.0,
      "end_time": 741366.0,
      "text": "that have personal weight to us --"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 741390.0,
      "end_time": 743966.0,
      "text": "ideas like blame and punishment or eyewitness memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 743990.0,
      "end_time": 746154.0,
      "text": "These are important things in our daily lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 748153.0,
      "end_time": 753154.0,
      "text": "Now, the beauty of linguistic diversity is that it reveals to us"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 753178.0,
      "end_time": 757125.0,
      "text": "just how ingenious and how flexible the human mind is."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 757775.0,
      "end_time": 762305.0,
      "text": "Human minds have invented not one cognitive universe, but 7,000 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 762330.0,
      "end_time": 764688.0,
      "text": "there are 7,000 languages spoken around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 766100.0,
      "end_time": 767687.0,
      "text": "And we can create many more --"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 767711.0,
      "end_time": 770794.0,
      "text": "languages, of course, are living things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 770818.0,
      "end_time": 774584.0,
      "text": "things that we can hone and change to suit our needs."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 775786.0,
      "end_time": 779268.0,
      "text": "The tragic thing is that we're losing so much of this linguistic diversity"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 779293.0,
      "end_time": 780444.0,
      "text": "all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 780468.0,
      "end_time": 782360.0,
      "text": "We're losing about one language a week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 782384.0,
      "end_time": 783850.0,
      "text": "and by some estimates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 783874.0,
      "end_time": 787141.0,
      "text": "half of the world's languages will be gone in the next hundred years."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 787966.0,
      "end_time": 790788.0,
      "text": "And the even worse news is that right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 790812.0,
      "end_time": 794520.0,
      "text": "almost everything we know about the human mind and human brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 794544.0,
      "end_time": 799572.0,
      "text": "is based on studies of usually American English-speaking undergraduates"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 799596.0,
      "end_time": 800920.0,
      "text": "at universities."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 802742.0,
      "end_time": 806275.0,
      "text": "That excludes almost all humans. Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 806299.0,
      "end_time": 811270.0,
      "text": "So what we know about the human mind is actually incredibly narrow and biased,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 811294.0,
      "end_time": 814530.0,
      "text": "and our science has to do better."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 817987.0,
      "end_time": 820246.0,
      "text": "I want to leave you with this final thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 820270.0,
      "end_time": 823783.0,
      "text": "I've told you about how speakers of different languages think differently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 823807.0,
      "end_time": 827910.0,
      "text": "but of course, that's not about how people elsewhere think."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 827115.0,
      "end_time": 828534.0,
      "text": "It's about how you think."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 828558.0,
      "end_time": 832164.0,
      "text": "It's how the language that you speak shapes the way that you think."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 833700.0,
      "end_time": 835646.0,
      "text": "And that gives you the opportunity to ask,"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 835670.0,
      "end_time": 837741.0,
      "text": "\"Why do I think the way that I do?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 837765.0,
      "end_time": 839361.0,
      "text": "\"How could I think differently?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 839908.0,
      "end_time": 841273.0,
      "text": "And also,"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 841297.0,
      "end_time": 843240.0,
      "text": "\"What thoughts do I wish to create?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 843842.0,
      "end_time": 845100.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 845250.0,
      "end_time": 847781.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}